# HOW TO CREATE EXTERNAL CSS

With an external style sheet, you can change the look of an entire website by changing just one file!
in this we are having two files.
1. html file.
2. css file.

1. HTML file code:- 
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
<title>
this is external CSS</title>
</hread>
<body>
<marquee> HELLO WORLD !!</marquee>
<h1> This is H1 tag</h1>
<br>
<p> THIs is the paragraph</p>
</body>
</html>

2. CSS FILE. (saved as "style.css")
NOTE: its important that the notepad file should save as '.css'
body{
	background-color: blue;
}
h1 {color: white;
	text-align: center;
}
p{color: pink;
	text-align:right;
}
marquee{
	color: black;
	}
